  "text": "Apache Kafka consumer group partition assignment strategies are implemented as Java classes in the clients module. The architecture consists of a base interface ConsumerPartitionAssignor in clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/ConsumerPartitionAssignor.java, which is implemented by an abstract base class AbstractPartitionAssignor in clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/AbstractPartitionAssignor.java. This abstract class provides common functionality for partition assignors, including rack-aware assignment logic and partition counting utilities.\n\nFour concrete assignor implementations are provided:\n\n1. RangeAssignor (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/RangeAssignor.java) - Works on a per-topic basis, laying out available partitions in numeric order and consumers in lexicographic order, dividing partitions evenly with the first consumers getting extra partitions if needed.\n\n2. RoundRobinAssignor (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/RoundRobinAssignor.java) - Lays out all available partitions and consumers, then performs round-robin assignment. When all consumer subscriptions are identical, partitions are uniformly distributed with ownership counts within one across all consumers.\n\n3. StickyAssignor (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/StickyAssignor.java) - Guarantees balanced assignment and preserves existing assignments during reassignment to minimize overhead. It extends AbstractStickyAssignor and uses eager rebalancing protocol.\n\n4. CooperativeStickyAssignor (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/CooperativeStickyAssignor.java) - A cooperative version of StickyAssignor that allows for cooperative rebalancing while maintaining the same sticky assignment logic. It also extends AbstractStickyAssignor but returns RebalanceProtocol.COOPERATIVE for supportedProtocols().\n\nBoth StickyAssignor and CooperativeStickyAssignor extend AbstractStickyAssignor (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/AbstractStickyAssignor.java), which provides the core sticky assignment algorithm implementation."
}

